{
  "stem": "2460.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had to watch it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Very, very, afraid.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Very frightening.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So OK, we were in Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The situation in Mauthausen was very, very bad, like I said, because of the German kapos.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were there till end of April.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Before-- days before we were evacuated, we don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't know then they dropped bombs on the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, we thought that they are the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They wanted to destroy us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They bombed the camp.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Bodies were flying all over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "People were killed all over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And people were grabbing human flesh and cooking the human flesh.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this was also something that we children, we couldn't take it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Most of-- I don't remember that-- none of us from the young people, they took human flesh and cooked the human flesh.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the older, they took.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I saw with my eyes that they grabbed from the wires human flesh, killed people, and they were cooking them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This  was almost end of the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But from there, we were evacuated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I think they were evacuating Mauthausen to a forest.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were walking about three days, 60-odd kilometers from Mauthausen through the city of Linz to Gunskirchen. 60-some kilometers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "On the second day, we were crossing a big bridge on the Donau.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we were about 3,000 in each transport, walking. 3,000 prisoners, maybe five or six German soldiers just watching us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were walking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we were on a bridge.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I can't remember exactly the name, but I always see [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I saw the name [NON-ENGLISH] somewhere.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there were Hungarian, Romanian, and German soldiers coming from the other side of the bridge.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And when I saw Hungarian soldiers, we were asking them, maybe they can throw us a piece of bread or something.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they looked very bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
